info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued October 25 at 2:40PM CDT until October 28 at 7:40PM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Yellow River at Babcock affecting Wood County. For the Yellow River...including Babcock...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS AFTERNOON TO SATURDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Yellow River at Babcock. * WHEN...From this afternoon to Saturday evening. * IMPACTS...At 15.6 feet, Floodwaters are near a couple of homes in the Babcock area near Highway 173. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 2:00 PM CDT Wednesday the stage was 12.6 feet. - Bankfull stage is 10.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 2:00 PM CDT Wednesday was 12.6 feet. - Forecast...The river will rise to 15.8 feet tomorrow morning. It will then fall below flood stage tomorrow afternoon to 9.2 feet Friday morning. It will rise above flood stage to 12.1 feet early Saturday morning. It will then fall below flood stage again early Saturday morning. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued late tonight.
